         <pb facs="1866_02_15_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_J_Staehelin_Wattwil_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>J. STAEHELIN<lb/>WATTWIL<lb/> Messrs. L. Kniffler +Co in
                (Nagasaki)<lb/>Yokohama<lb/>Wattwyl, 15th February 1866<lb/>I acknowledge the
                pleasant receipt of your esteemed <lb/>letter from 16th Dec. 65 and extracted from
                this <lb/>£. 3,26.9.12.6 monthly view s. London Joint Stock<lb/>Bank in
                London<lb/>which I credit conformly s. b. f. to your Nagasaki <lb/>house at 4/6¼
                with $1444„28..<lb/>I took good note of the remainder of your <lb/>esteemed letter.
                Once the economic situation <lb/>becomes more favourable again, i.e. when lower<lb/>
                commodity prices bring about lower purchase<lb/>costs, I hope to be able to send
                something <lb/>there again _<lb/>In the meantime I will be pleased to receive your
                <lb/>kind reports occasionally + am signing<lb/>Yours respectfully :<lb/>J.
                Staehelin</p>
